Posts.Content: Yes, it is possible! It happened to my sister; found a lump a couple of years ago and further imaging (3d mammo, etc.) showed that it was not a problem, but it was never biopsied. Now she is finding out that it was cancerous all along. Try not to worrry, but keep after the docs until you are satisfied with their answers and trust your instincts-take care!
Posts.Title: Is it possible to not find cancer?
